      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Boy Scout Lesson</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Harvey Marshak letter, commenting on August 29 article on loss in support for Boy Scouts following Supreme Court decision upholding organization's ban on homosexuals, says companies caught in Catch-22 bind will not desert boys by withholding donations</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Scouts' Successful Ban on Gays Is Followed by Loss in Support'' (front page, Aug. 29):</p>
        <p>Companies caught in a Catch-22 bind by the Boy Scouts of America's ban on homosexuality will not be deserting the boys by withholding donations.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Scouts' Successful Ban on Gays Is Followed by Loss in Support'' (front page, Aug. 29):</p>
        <p>Companies caught in a Catch-22 bind by the Boy Scouts of America's ban on homosexuality will not be deserting the boys by withholding donations.</p>
        <p>Children learn by example. The example of standing by one's principles rather than opting for fun or the support of fun regardless of the rights of others will stand these boys well as they become adults and are called upon to set their own examples.</p>
        <p>HARVEY MARSHAK  New York, Aug. 29, 2000</p>
      </block>
